Siemens to start selling DRAM chips in Japan - paper . Siemens AG will enter Japan ' s dynamic random access memory ( DRAM ) chip market after increasing its stake in a joint venture with Fuji Electric Co Ltd earlier this year , a Japanese newspaper said on Wednesday . Siemens will import Siemens - made DRAM chips from Europe from next year , the Nihon Keizai Shimbun economic daily said . Siemens spent several hundred million yen in July to increase its stake in Fuji Electronic Components Ltd to 80 percent from 50 percent , the paper said . Spokesmen for the companies were not immediately available for comment . 
